areaTree0.PointDescription:
Enables long-range transmit to and from an activated spacerift. 
Created before the Cataclysm, it represents the pinnacle of Aidan technology. Banges Tech is now responsible for the construction and maintenance of spacerift everywhere, allowing Wanderers to go anywhere they want to go through the spacerifts.

areaTree1.PointDescription:
The Omnium Tower built in the Astra region, may be used as a portal node.
When there's an energy shortage, it stands in as a backup to help power the shelter. Formerly a tourist site, but was forgotten alongside Astra as both slipped into abandonment. After the Astra Shelter was built, the tower got an overhaul into what it is today.

areaTree2.PointDescription:
The Omnium Tower built in the Banges region, may be used as a portal node.
The construction of the tower signaled the emergence of Bangesâ€”or at least what the guidebook said.

areaTree3.PointDescription:
The Omnium Tower built in the Navia region, may be used as a portal node.
Since the area has been abandoned, the tower's main purpose is to provide power for the marvelous flying island of Cetus Island.

areaTree4.PointDescription:
The Omnium Tower built in the Crown region, may be used as a portal node.
According to the pact signed by Mr. Kim and Hykros, the latter will supply sufficient power to the mines, and the mines will reciprocate with premium ore in return. The agreement propelled the area to the prosperous development it enjoys today.

areaTree5.PointDescription:
The Omnium Tower built in the Warren Snowfield, may be used as a portal node.
Standing in the white wilderness, it provides guidance for the Wanderers in the blizzard. Only by observing closely can it be found that the major structure of the Omnium Tower has been firmly icebound due to the influence of the environment.

FB01_D.PointDescription: Tunnels going who-knows-where with caverns filled with unknown, dangerous creatures. Everything about this place is terrifying.

FB03_D.PointDescription: This shattered ruin contained explosives from the past.

FB04_D.PointDescription: Keep everything you encountered in this ruin to yourself, lest you want to be trapped here forever.

FB05_D.PointDescription: Do you have any idea how treacherous this place is? It's the abyss of no return since you have no way of turning back now.

FB06_D.PointDescription: No technologies or civilizations here, just leftover air of desolation and unknown dangers.

NPC_Shop_Gem.PointDescription: An incredibly lucky Wanderer who always seems to pick up quality items.

NPC_Shop_Food001-01.PointDescription: A kind old woman who loves to collect Food and sell them to the needy.

NPC_Shop_Food001_02.PointDescription: The top Food Appraiser for Banges. Any food meeting his approval is both amazingly delicious and expensive.

NPC_Shop_Food002_01.PointDescription: The top foodie on Astra. Paying her is the only way you can enjoy her cooking.

NPC_Shop_Food002_02.PointDescription: Aspires to become the greatest chef on Aida and tries to perfect her recipes nonstop, putting the failures up for sale.

NPC_Shop_Grocer_01.PointDescription: Dreams of opening his own biggest grocery store in Banges without having to pay taxes somehow.

NPC_Shop_Equip02.PointDescription: Her husband died in a massive Ravager raid three years ago. The resilient woman has been running the family ever since.

NPC_Shop_Weapon001_01.PointDescription: He held a crush on Maria since childhood, but was too timid to make a move. He started the weapon dealership just to make connections with her.

NPC_EquipFragmentShop_01.PointDescription: Guess what's in his backpack? Oh look, the weapon shards you need!

FB02_D.PointDescription: Ever heard of the Curse of the Ruin? That's the hex you get when you just barge into ruins recklessly.

FB07_D.PointDescription: Here, there is only death knell and no salvation. You'll regret coming.

FB25_D.PointDescription: As long as you're alive, you'll feel pain. Glad to see you, my favorite patron.

FB09_D.PointDescription: Life is an endless cycle of past and future. Do you belong to the future or the past?

Boss_2.PointDescription: The most powerful artificial life of Astra, Robarg, slumbers in the Tomb of Thorns. She was the proud handiwork of a certain biologist who's been waiting for her master's return ever since being abandoned. The long wait in the radioactive environment has caused profound changes to Robarg. She's lost her gentleness and aberrated into a savage, malicious giant carnivorous plant.

B_AreaVolume_Spawn_Level1_03.PointDescription: Barrenstown has been overrun by aberrant creatures. Look out for Bloodspine, an extremely lethal presence.

Boss_3.PointDescription: In the north summits of Banges Industries dwells a composite creature created by the Heirs of Aida called Apophis. It's in charge of guarding the Heirs' base in the high mountains. Designed based on the genes of aberrant panthers, Apophis combines the agility of the Panthera species and the artificial intelligence of composite creatures. After the Heirs of Aida modified its forepaws into machinery paws, Apophis has now possessed mighty power that could tear up the earth.

TeamBoss_10.PointDescription: Lady Lucia, the leader of the Hyenas and celebrated "Queen of the World," demands sophistication and elegance in everything she encounters, which is why she chose the Rose Garden as her castle. Lady Lucia values beauty above all else, and deems herself to be the most beautiful woman in the world. She believes she possesses the most sublime figure, the fairest complexion and the most alluring looks. She commands the Hyenas to address her as "Your Majesty," adorns herself with feathers and lace, and carries a whip, which she considers the most graceful and suitable weapon.

Homeland_Boss_4.PointDescription: Prototypical replica created by the Heirs of Aida from the data of amalgam beasts, released under the premise of balancing the ecology on Artificial Island. Its signature rip claws are not to be underestimated.

Homeland_Boss_5.PointDescription: Prototypical replica created from the data of mutated artificial lifeforms, released under the premise of balancing the ecology on Artificial Island. Obviously, plants like this are not at the bottom of the food chain here.

Homeland_Boss_6.PointDescription: Prototypical replica created from the data of base-guarding animals, released under the premise of balancing the ecology on Artificial Island. Its two heads constantly bicker over how to survive in the new environment.

Homeland_Boss_7.PointDescription: Prototypical replica created from the data of cybertoads, released under the premise of balancing the ecology on Artificial Island. You'll never have to worry about this place being infested by bugs.

Breakfate_Boss_01.PointDescription: It was originally an advanced aberrant but was later modified by Dr. Burkman with ATK boosting devices added to it. However, it became more violent and hard to control after the modification and was thus abandoned.

Breakfate_Boss_02.PointDescription: A humanlike armor made by the Ravagers from an old aircraft with a Gatling gun on its left wrist and an electromagnetic cutting weapon on its right wrist. It can temporarily hover in the air.

Breakfate_Boss_03.PointDescription: The Hyenas invented a simple yet fairly powerful mech with the limited resources they had on hand. The cannons on its shoulders are capable of suppressive fire and bombardment at the same time. And the cooling devices on its arms emit steam that can be used to attack enemies during combat.

Vera_Boss_2.PointDescription: In order to unravel the mystery of Grayspace Entities, the Department of Science and Technology of Mirroria launched a project codenamed "Listener," which even attempted to bioengineer Grayspace Entities. "Rudolph, Test Subject 6", a fusion of Grayspace Entity and native Veran creatures, was the end result. It remains to be seen if Rudolph is the key to solving the crisis, or if the Pandora's Box has been opened.

Vera_Boss_3.PointDescription: A killing machine created by evil forces before the Cataclysm. It was once used for looting resources, but the Cataclysm wiped out its evil masters. For decades, it has been wandering in Vera.

VeraCity_Taxi_JieDai.PointDescription: One of the cruiser stops of the public transportation system that is very well received by the residents of Mirroria. The Mirroria Aerial Port is what connects Mirroria and the Yellowrock Desert together, and must be passed if entering and exiting the city of Mirroria. The reception center, citizen service center, and many other public service stations are set up here.

VeraCity_Taxi_Centre.PointDescription: One of the cruiser stops of the public transportation system that is very well received by the residents of Mirroria. The Furnace Core Site is located directly below the Vera Tower of Fantasy, and is used to study the Abyssant Crystamax. It is not open to the general public.

VeraCity_Taxi_A2.PointDescription: One of the cruiser stops of the public transportation system that is very well received by the residents of Mirroria. The Oasis Club is the main recreational place for the residents of Mirroria. If you wanna relax and have some fun with your friends, the Oasis Club will not disappoint.

VeraCity_Taxi_A3.PointDescription: A well-loved public transport and cruiser stop for the residents of Mirroria. Probably because it is so fast and convenient, the opinion box is often filled with letters that say: "Please consider making my address a potential new stop!"

VeraCity_Taxi_A4.PointDescription: One of the cruiser stops of the public transportation system that is very well received by the residents of Mirroria. The Asset Management Center is a facility that provides asset management services for the residents of Mirroria. Stop by here if you have any questions about managing your personal assets, as there's a solution no matter who you are.

VeraCity_Taxi_B4.PointDescription: One of the cruiser stops of the public transportation system that is very well received by the residents of Mirroria. A lab that studies Omnium and other dangerous substances. Due to the specificity of the facility, all personnel require authorization to both enter and exit this area.

VeraCity_Metro_Line1_2.PointDescription: The public transportation system and one of the stops of the subway that is very well received by the residents of Mirroria. Among the hustle and bustle, the floating carriages are also a sight to behold in the city. Cruising between subway stations has become one of the bucket list items of tourists.

Vera_Airport.PointDescription: In response to the threat of the Grayspace Entities, a huge defense force field was set up on the surface, making it impossible to travel directly to the city from the ground. An airship must be taken in order to travel between Mirroria and the Outpost.

Breakfate_Boss_01_team.PointDescription: It was originally an advanced aberrant but was later modified by Dr. Burkman with ATK boosting devices added to it. However, it became more violent and hard to control after the modification and was thus abandoned.

Breakfate_Boss_02_team.PointDescription: A humanlike armor made by the Ravagers from an old aircraft with a Gatling gun on its left wrist and an electromagnetic cutting weapon on its right wrist. It can temporarily hover in the air.

Breakfate_Boss_03_team.PointDescription: The Hyenas invented a simple yet fairly powerful mech with the limited resources they had on hand. The cannons on its shoulders are capable of suppressive fire and bombardment at the same time. And the cooling devices on its arms emit steam that can be used to attack enemies during combat.
